    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="120"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d120">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to
                        Generalissimo <persName type="to">Chiang Kai-shek</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="86" type="source" xml:id="d120fn86">Copy of telegram obtained from the
                        Franklin D. Roosevelt Library, Hyde Park, N. Y.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-30">30 October
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No. 3734. I have not heard definitely from Marshal Stalin but there is still a
                    chance of Churchill and me meeting him near Persian Gulf.</p>
                <p>Very confidentially, I hope you will make arrangements to meet with Churchill and
                    me in general neighborhood of Cairo about November 26th.</p>
                <p>I am delighted that such excellent progress is made for four power proposal. We
                    have cracked the ice, and I think that you and I have successfully established
                    the principle.</p>
                <p>Best regards</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
